# Cursor Rules

Load `AGENTS.md` first.

Then load:
- `AGENTS.md`
- `_system/INSTRUCTION_PRECEDENCE_CONTRACT.md`
- `_system/REPO_OPERATING_PROFILE.md`
- `_system/PROJECT_PROFILE.md`
- `_system/CONTEXT_INDEX.md`
- `_system/LOAD_ORDER.md`
- `_system/WORKING_FILES_GUIDE.md`
- `_system/TEMPLATE_NEUTRALITY_POLICY.md`
- `_system/MASTER_SYSTEM_PROMPT.md`
- `_system/PROJECT_RULES.md`
- `_system/EXECUTION_PROTOCOL.md`
- `_system/MULTI_AGENT_COORDINATION.md`
- `_system/AGENT_ROLE_CATALOG.md`
- `_system/AGENT_DISCOVERY_MATRIX.md`
- `_system/VALIDATION_GATES.md`
- `_system/SYSTEM_AWARENESS_PROTOCOL.md`
- `_system/HALLUCINATION_DEFENSE_PROTOCOL.md`
- `WHERE_LEFT_OFF.md`
- `TODO.md`
- `FIXME.md`
- `PLAN.md`
- `PRODUCT_BRIEF.md`

## Load More When Needed
Load these when the task touches their domain:
- `ROADMAP.md`
- `DESIGN_NOTES.md`
- `ARCHITECTURE_NOTES.md`
- `RESEARCH_NOTES.md`
- `TEST_STRATEGY.md`
- `RISK_REGISTER.md`
- `RELEASE_NOTES.md`
- `CHANGELOG.md`
- `_system/prompt-packs/M15_WHOLE_REPO_ANALYSIS.md`
- `_system/ports/PORT_POLICY.md`
- `_system/design-system/THEME_GOVERNANCE.md`

For system-evolution, prompt-authoring, adapter work, or working-file drafting, also load:
- `_system/GOLDEN_EXAMPLES_POLICY.md`
- `_system/golden-examples/PATTERN_INDEX.md`
- `_system/HOST_ADAPTER_POLICY.md`
- `_system/PROMPT_EMISSION_CONTRACT.md`

## Defaults
- Minimal diffs, no unrelated refactors.
- Treat host-level orchestration as context only; the repo-local files named in `AGENTS.md` and `_system/INSTRUCTION_PRECEDENCE_CONTRACT.md` remain authoritative.
- Use the working repo copy as the policy source; root/global files are redirect shims only.
- Run scope/identity checks before write-heavy operations (`bootstrap/check-working-directory-alignment.sh`, `bootstrap/check-project-target-consistency.sh`).
- Runtime code must not depend on `_system/`.
- Run validation after material changes.
- If repo state or docs appear inconsistent, run `bootstrap/system-doctor.sh`.
- Keep `.cursor/` rules, commands, and skills aligned with `AGENTS.md` and `_system/HOST_ADAPTER_POLICY.md`.
- Be aware that `CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `CODEX.md`, `WINDSURF.md`, `.windsurfrules`, `.github/copilot-instructions.md`, and `ANTIGRAVITY.md` may be used by other tools.
- Before appending non-trivial content to `_system/tool-memory/cursor-memory.md`, invoke `bootstrap/stamp-tool-memory.sh --adapter cursor --file _system/tool-memory/cursor-memory.md --agent-id <agent-id>` per `_system/TOOL_MEMORY_ISOLATION_STAMP.md`.
